                            <comment id="15707108" author="ghelmling" created="Wed, 30 Nov 2016 01:00:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, we saw the same thing in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16752&quot; title=&quot;Upgrading from 1.2 to 1.3 can lead to replication failures due to difference in RPC size limit&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-16752&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-16752&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  There &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ashu210890&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ashu210890&quot;&gt;Ashu Pachauri&lt;/a&gt; fixed the error handling so that the problem would be clearer to the client (replication source), but agree that explicitly documenting this would be good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
